.TH "snd_dma_alloc_pages" 9 "snd_dma_alloc_pages" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
snd_dma_alloc_pages \- allocate the buffer area according to the given type
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" snd_dma_alloc_pages
.BI "(int type "  ","
.BI "struct device *device "  ","
.BI "size_t size "  ","
.BI "struct snd_dma_buffer *dmab "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "type" 12
the DMA buffer type
.IP "device" 12
the device pointer
.IP "size" 12
the buffer size to allocate
.IP "dmab" 12
buffer allocation record to store the allocated data
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Calls the memory-allocator function for the corresponding
buffer type.
.SH "RETURN"
Zero if the buffer with the given size is allocated successfully,
otherwise a negative value on error.
